gomodel:SYNGO_2097  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.6-8 The use of HAV peptides were shown by the authors to disrupt the homophilic interactions between specific cadherin subtypes. Infusion of N-cad HAV peptides does not alter basal synaptic signal transduction, but interferes with LTP induction (not maintenance) with different protocols. N-cad HAV peptides do not interfere with PPI, NMDAR EPSPs or postsynaptic depolarization mechanisms.. Experimental description: \"Hippocampal slices were prepared using a Stoelting tissue chopper from young (6- to 8-week-old) adult male Sprague-Dawley rats ....\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
